//! Rational Canonical Form (RCF / Frobenius Normal Form) over Q.
//!
//! Computes the unique RCF orbit representative for a rational matrix,
//! satisfying D.CHAIN.ORBIT.1: two matrices in the same GL_n(Q) conjugacy
//! class produce the identical invariant factor sequence.
//!
//! Algorithm: characteristic matrix (xI - A) → Smith Normal Form over Q[x]
//! → invariant factors d₁(x) | d₂(x) | ... | dₖ(x) → companion blocks.
//!
//! For antisymmetric matrices (Delta), the symplectic structure guarantees
//! that every GL_n(Q) conjugacy class contains a symplectically canonical
//! representative computable in O(n³) rational operations.
//!
//! Register: D.CHAIN.ORBIT.1, OI.FOUND.1.

